Detection Logic

Detect root account logins via SSH.

Splunk Query
index=linux sourcetype=secure "Accepted password for root"
| rex "from (?<src_ip>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+)"
| stats count by src_ip host
Why It's Suspicious

Best practice:

PermitRootLogin no

So if you see root login events, investigate immediately.
